1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
This prompted several of the finest families in the area to sell their homes at a loss and move on.
2
00:00:01,335 --> 00:00:08,425
As so often happens, the do-care families caught the don't-care attitude from their don't-care neighbors.
3
00:00:08,614 --> 00:00:15,945
Everyone, that is, except Harry L. Harry, did care, and he decided to crusade for a fine neighborhood.
4
00:00:16,134 --> 00:00:19,304
Harry began by calling together some friends.
5
00:00:19,574 --> 00:00:29,465
He pointed out that this subdivision had tremendous potential, but that something must be done now or the area would soon be a strictly second-class neighborhood.
6
00:00:29,815 --> 00:00:33,545
Harry's enthusiasm and initiative quickly won support.
7
00:00:33,734 --> 00:00:36,824
Soon there were clean-up-the-vacant-lots projects.
8
00:00:37,014 --> 00:00:38,985
Garden clubs were organized.
9
00:00:39,094 --> 00:00:41,865
A massive tree-planting project was started.
10
00:00:41,974 --> 00:00:44,425
A playground was built for the youngsters.
11
00:00:44,534 --> 00:00:47,223
A community swimming pool was constructed.
12
00:00:47,494 --> 00:00:50,824
The don't-care families became eager supporters.
13
00:00:51,014 --> 00:00:54,824
The whole subdivision took on new life and new sparkle.
14
00:00:55,014 --> 00:00:58,184
It's really a pleasure now to drive through that community.
15
00:00:58,214 --> 00:01:00,985
It shows what a Crusader can do.
16
00:01:01,654 --> 00:01:08,264
Do you feel your business should develop a new department, make a new product, or in some other way expand?
17
00:01:08,454 --> 00:01:10,585
Well then, Crusade for it.
18
00:01:10,774 --> 00:01:12,985
Feel your church needs a new building?
19
00:01:13,094 --> 00:01:14,345
Crusade for it.
20
00:01:14,454 --> 00:01:17,704
Would you like your children's school to have better equipment?
21
00:01:17,895 --> 00:01:20,184
Crusade and get it for them.
22
00:01:20,534 --> 00:01:22,345
And you can bank on this.
23
00:01:22,534 --> 00:01:29,304
While Crusades may start out as one-man Crusades, if the idea behind the Enterprise is good,
24
00:01:29,494 --> 00:01:31,545
soon you'll have lots of support.
25
00:01:32,214 --> 00:01:35,385
Be an Activationist and Crusade.
26
00:01:35,494 --> 00:01:37,784
2.
27
00:01:38,134 --> 00:01:46,345
Be a Volunteer Each of us has been in situations in which we wanted to volunteer for some activity but didn't.
28
00:01:46,454 --> 00:01:46,985
Why?
29
00:01:47,254 --> 00:01:48,505
Because of fear.
30
00:01:48,694 --> 00:01:54,425
Not fear that we couldn't accomplish the task, but rather fear of what our associates would say.
31
00:01:54,694 --> 00:02:03,065
The fear of being laughed at, of being called an eager beaver, of being accused of bucking for a raise holds many people back.
32
00:02:04,134 --> 00:02:08,824
It's natural to want to belong, to be accepted, to have group approval.
33
00:02:09,014 --> 00:02:13,145
But ask yourself, which group do I want to have accept me?
34
00:02:13,414 --> 00:02:20,025
The group that laughs because it is secretly jealous, or the group that is making progress by doing things?
35
00:02:20,375 --> 00:02:22,425
The right choice is obvious.
36
00:02:23,094 --> 00:02:25,224
The volunteer stands out.
37
00:02:25,414 --> 00:02:27,545
He receives special attention.
